name: The HOPE Tee Shirt - Supporting Breast Cancer
description:
This shirt was created in 2010 by owner Dani Davis and Graphic Artist, King Carter. The two created the design after Elusion Clothing participated in an event supporting breast cancer research. The shirt usually sells in October, Breast Cancer Awareness Month. 

Once it is removed, we constantly get emails about the shirt, often selling it privately. We want the shirt to be available all year. Breast Cancer survivors get 50% off the shirts by entering the code SURVIVOR at checkout(please purchase the shirt by itself to use the code). 

We wanted to do our part to help those directly affected by the disease. The shirt has done extremely well. All we pay for is the printing cost of the shirt. With the rest, we used to donate to Susan G. Komen, but we hope to work closely with families affected where we can give some money to help with medical bills, groceries, transportation, etc. Buy one, buy one hundred. Support the cause. 

Available in three colors, mens sizes and women's
